Design and implement a console-based banking system in Go that models real-world banking operations using structs and methods only.
The system must simulate account management, transactions, and basic banking rules without using slices, maps, arrays, or databases.



üß± Core Entities (Design Requirement)

1Ô∏è‚É£ Customer

Each customer represents a real bank user.

Fields (example-level guidance, not mandatory):
	‚Ä¢	CustomerID
	‚Ä¢	FullName
	‚Ä¢	Age
	‚Ä¢	PhoneNumber
	‚Ä¢	IsActive

Rules:
	‚Ä¢	Customer must be 18+
	‚Ä¢	Inactive customers cannot perform transactions

‚∏ª

2Ô∏è‚É£ BankAccount

Each customer owns exactly one bank account.

Fields:
	‚Ä¢	AccountNumber
	‚Ä¢	AccountType (Savings / Current)
	‚Ä¢	Balance
	‚Ä¢	IsFrozen

Rules:
	‚Ä¢	Minimum balance:
	‚Ä¢	Savings: ‚Çπ1,000
	‚Ä¢	Current: ‚Çπ5,000
	‚Ä¢	Frozen accounts cannot:
	‚Ä¢	Withdraw
	‚Ä¢	Transfer
	‚Ä¢	Balance must never go negative

‚∏ª

3Ô∏è‚É£ Bank

Represents the bank itself.

Fields:
	‚Ä¢	BankName
	‚Ä¢	IFSCCode
	‚Ä¢	TotalFunds
	‚Ä¢	Fixed number of customers (example: exactly 3 customers as struct fields)

‚ö†Ô∏è Since slices/maps are not allowed, customers must be stored like:
	‚Ä¢	Customer1
	‚Ä¢	Customer2
	‚Ä¢	Customer3

‚∏ª

4Ô∏è‚É£ Transaction

Each transaction records a single operation.

Fields:
	‚Ä¢	TransactionID
	‚Ä¢	AccountNumber
	‚Ä¢	TransactionType (Deposit / Withdraw / Transfer)
	‚Ä¢	Amount
	‚Ä¢	Status (Success / Failed)

‚ö†Ô∏è Only the last transaction needs to be stored per account.

‚∏ª

‚öôÔ∏è Required Operations (Methods)

Customer-Level Methods
	‚Ä¢	ActivateCustomer()
	‚Ä¢	DeactivateCustomer()
	‚Ä¢	IsEligibleForBanking()

‚∏ª

Account-Level Methods
	‚Ä¢	Deposit(amount)
	‚Ä¢	Withdraw(amount)
	‚Ä¢	GetBalance()
	‚Ä¢	FreezeAccount()
	‚Ä¢	UnfreezeAccount()

Validation must include:
	‚Ä¢	Account status
	‚Ä¢	Customer status
	‚Ä¢	Minimum balance rule

‚∏ª

Bank-Level Methods
	‚Ä¢	OpenAccount(customer)
	‚Ä¢	CloseAccount(accountNumber)
	‚Ä¢	TransferFunds(fromAccount, toAccount, amount)
	‚Ä¢	GetBankTotalFunds()

‚∏ª

Transaction-Level Methods
	‚Ä¢	CreateTransaction()
	‚Ä¢	MarkSuccess()
	‚Ä¢	MarkFailed(reason)

‚∏ª

üîÅ Application Flow (Simulation)
	1.	Create a Bank instance
	2.	Create fixed number of customers
	3.	Open accounts for customers
	4.	Perform:
	‚Ä¢	Deposits
	‚Ä¢	Withdrawals
	‚Ä¢	Transfers
	5.	Freeze one account and show failure cases
	6.	Deactivate one customer and block transactions
	7.	Print:
	‚Ä¢	Account balances
	‚Ä¢	Last transaction status
	‚Ä¢	Bank total funds

‚∏ª

‚ùó Error Handling Rules
	‚Ä¢	Withdrawal more than balance ‚Üí ‚ùå fail
	‚Ä¢	Transfer from frozen account ‚Üí ‚ùå fail
	‚Ä¢	Deposit into closed account ‚Üí ‚ùå fail
	‚Ä¢	Underage customer ‚Üí ‚ùå fail
	‚Ä¢	Minimum balance violation ‚Üí ‚ùå fail

Each failure must:
	‚Ä¢	Create a failed transaction
	‚Ä¢	Print a clear reason
